content: 22  /  31   There is a tiny yellow daffodil, The butterfly can see it from afar, Although one summer evening's dew could fill Its little cup twice over, ere the star Had called the lazy shepherd to his fold, And be no prodigal.	by Oscar Wilde (oscar Fingal O'flahertie Wilde) Found in Daffodils Quotes, Share to:
contentWithMarkup:
There is a tiny yellow daffodil,
 The butterfly can see it from afar,
  Although one summer evening's dew could fill
   Its little cup twice over, ere the star
    Had called the lazy shepherd to his fold,
     And be no prodigal.
